imdb.title: Bara Ou no Souretsu
imdb.plot: The war for the throne of England, as seen through the eyes of the deformed anti-hero Richard III.

episodes.title: Wars of the Roses
episodes.plot: Civil war grips Medieval England as the houses of York and Lancaster vie for the throne. Richard, the Duke of York's youngest son, wants nothing more than to see his father crowned king, but he struggles with a secret that he fears to confront.

episodes.title: Father Is My Light
episodes.plot: The Duke of York has seized the capital and the throne, but he must still overcome Queen Margaret's army if he hopes to be crowned king. Richard, imprisoned in the Tower of London, can only speculate about the fortunes of war.

episodes.title: I Am the Shadow, the Darkness Behind the Light
episodes.plot: The Duke of York's death is a blow both to Richard and to the Yorkist cause, but an unforeseen setback gives the Earl of Warwick and Edward time to rally their forces. How will Richard face the coming battle and a world without the duke?

episodes.title: I'm Afraid I'm Going to Lose the Answers I've Gotten and... Everything Else
episodes.plot: Edward, now king, enlists Richard to guard the secret of his affair with Elizabeth Woodville. Alone in the woods, Richard has an unexpected encounter that raises unsettling questions.

episodes.title: If I Don't Grab Your Hand, I Won't Have to Let Go
episodes.plot: The Earl of Warwick seethes at his humiliation and loss of power caused by King Edward's marriage. Meanwhile, Richard's time with the earl's daughter, Anne, raises new possibilities in the young duke's mind.

episodes.title: A man who has no awareness as king... A man who is not qualified to be king... Neither of them is fit for the throne.
episodes.plot: The Earl of Warwick plots rebellion, and tensions mount between George and King Edward. The king refuses to doubt his comrade or his brother, but his trust may cost him his crown.

episodes.title: Even if I sin...
episodes.plot: Richard and Catesby race to rescue the captive Edward, who has fallen into Warwick's hands. Meanwhile, Prince Edward is preoccupied with his position in England and his feelings for Richard.

episodes.title: Even alone, it wasn't frightening. Rather... the loneliness has been kind ever since losing Father.
episodes.plot: The Yorkist cause seems desperate with Warwick championing the Lancastrian cause and Henry back on the throne. Edward entrusts Richard to carry out a secret mission that could reverse their fortunes.

episodes.title: I remember when Christmas was approaching. The time when I lost Father.
episodes.plot: Richard and Catesby continue their mission to win George back to the Yorkist cause. Meanwhile, Henry laments his position as Warwick raises an army to prevent Edward's return.

episodes.title: My name is Richard Plantagenet.
episodes.plot: As Edward's and Warwick's forces finally clash, Richard races across the misty battlefield in search of King Henry, the target of his vengeance.

episodes.title: That is my... my punishment...
episodes.plot: Warwick is dead and his army scattered, but Edward and the Yorkist forces still have to contend with Margaret's French army. How will Richard fare in battle after an unsettling encounter with Henry?

episodes.title: Richard is dead, died alone in the woods that day.
episodes.plot: Richard stews in inner turmoil as Edward celebrates the Yorkist victory and George jockeys for position. When the question of the captive Henry's fate is raised, Richard is forced to make an irrevocable choice.

episodes.title: After all, this body is just a prison of the soul...
episodes.plot: Memories of war fade as Edward IV celebrates his prosperous reign, but all is not well. Between the king's mysterious new mistress and George's open dissatisfaction, Richard may be force to act once more.

episodes.title: Good night. Brother.
episodes.plot: Richard and Buckingham have successfully framed George for a sorcerous plot against King Edward and now scheme to ensure he does not leave his prison cell alive. As Edward's health fails, the conspirators grow more urgent and more ruthless
